&lt;p&gt;I don&#39;t think that&#39;s the case. Both&nbsp; dictionary.com, and in my
Longman dictionary,&nbsp; list words like NURSE spelled with /3r/. Both
dictionaries represent the majority of American speakers.&nbsp; The
Cambridge dictionary lists it the same way. So most people will have
this issue. Yes, we can overcome the ambiguity with practice, but then
the spelling replicates the mistakes in TO, in which we have to learn
by context what sounds letters make, rather than have one unambiguous
representation.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
